<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>An EXCELLENT idea IMHO. Let's start a serious discussion.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Nafgar[CC]">Nafgar[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:29 a.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> An EXCELLENT idea IMHO. Let's start a serious discussion.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I know I can't spell (see:topic)

<BR>Anyhow, someone suggested once that on the PVP server monsters give 2X the experience that you would get on the normal servers. Before everyone starts dismissing this, remember that with the pvp server in P4, Verant has acknowledged PvPer's as a community of players, and has taken our wishes into consideration. Thusly, we can assume if we get a consensus from 90% of the pvpers on a topic, they might make it happen on *our* server. This goes for all topics, and not just this one.
<BR>The 2X experience idea is a good one. With the emphisis of the game on PvP, faction and guild wars, why not make monster killing more the means to and end, rather than the end itself. This would also make melee classes a little (only a little) more viable to play, more exp=quicker leveling=easier to get the equipment that a warrior would need.
<BR>In closing, we, as PvPer's, want to war with each other. We do not necessarily want to take monsters out of the game, but the fact of the matter is, we will be dying more. Correction, anyone not in my guild will be dying more :) So I say we make it easier to get exp, and I think this is one way to do it.
<BR>Nafgar[CC]-Geiger, if you ever chose to add color to my name, dont do it to this IP :)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
